Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with grape cluster symbol and Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 181, 1? Name Themison. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0630.15?
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1058)
